The assertion uses `.ToString()` — if the format changes (currency symbol, spacing, order of fields), this test breaks even though the summary data is correct.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — brittle string comparison via ToString()
Assert.AreEqual("Order ORD-001: 1 item(s), Total: $99.99", summary.ToString());
```

**Fix:** Assert on the structured properties of the summary object:

```csharp
Assert.AreEqual("ORD-001", summary.OrderId);
Assert.AreEqual(1, summary.ItemCount);
Assert.AreEqual(99.99m, summary.Total);
```

Or if string output is the actual requirement, compare against a known format method rather than calling `.ToString()` in the assertion.

**Risk if unfixed:** Any cosmetic formatting change breaks the test.

